DC Comics superstar writer Geoff Johns and the great director Richard Donner combine to tell this tale of another child of the doomed planet that gave us the Man of Steel, with terrific art from both Adam Kubert and Gary Frank. Promotional info for the collected edition - &quot;A rocket lands in Metropolis containing a boy that Superman thinks is from Krypton. Along with figuring out that that means to him, Superman must protect young Christopher Kent, who has become the most valuable child on the planet thanks to his immense power. Lex Luthor has his sights on him, assembling his own team of villains to nab Christopher. It all leads to an action-packed finale, as Superman and the new Superman Revenge Squad -- Lex Luthor, Bizarro, the Parasite and Metallo -- take on General Zod, Ursa and Non in a battle for Metropolis, the future of Krypton and Christopher Kent!&quot;

Originally told in the pages of Action Comics, this is the one-volume Hardcover edition with bonus materials and stories. This fantastic copy is digital and courtesy of Zone-Empire. All credit to those scanners for their efforts, please seed and enjoy! :-)
